-- Chile Government to Submit $63 Billion Budget Bill, Tercera Says
-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 2012-09-26T12:39:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-26/chile-government-to-submit-63-billion-budget-bill-tercera-says.html
Chile’s government will propose $63
billion of public spending in the 2013 budget bill that must be
sent to Congress this month, newspaper La Tercera  reported
today , citing Patricio Melero, president of the pro-government
UDI political party, and Christian Democrat Congressman Jose Miguel Ortiz.  Next year’s budget, which Ortiz said would boost
expenditures by 5 percent over 2012, will put emphasis on
education, health care, public safety and energy, the Santiago-
based newspaper reported, citing Finance Minister Felipe Larrain.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
